{'title': u'Please STOP making "smooth motion" the DEFAULT setting on all HDTVs.', 'url': 'https://www.change.org/p/hdtv-manufacturers-please-stop-making-smooth-motion-the-default-setting-on-all-hdtvs', 'abstract': u'Motion Interpolation was an effect that was created to reduce motion blur on HDTVs but a very unfortunate side effect of using this function is that is takes something shot at 24 fps or shot on film and makes it look like it was shot on video at 60i. In short, it takes the cinematic look out of any image and makes it look like soap opera shot on a cheap video camera.', 'meta': '{\'petition_comment\': u\'{\\\'petition_comments\\\': u\\\'{"items":[{"id":97289329,"comment":"I am a cinematographer and "smooth motion" is not the way the film makers want their movies presented.","created_at":"2014-10-27T04:41:42Z","user_id":171501669,"petition_id":2181244,"likes":27,"user":{"id":171501669,"slug":"171501669","first_name":"Claudio","last_name":"Miranda","short_display_name":"Claudio","display_name":"Claudio Miranda","city":"Los Angeles","state_code":"CA","country_code":"US","website":null,"locale":"en-US","description":null},"petition":{"id":2181244,"document_id":"2181244","ask":"Please STOP making "smooth motion" the DEFAULT setting on all HDTVs.","created_at":"2014-10-26T16:23:20Z","original_locale":"en-US","languages":["en"],"title":"HDTV Manufacturers: Please STOP making "smooth motion" the DEFAULT setting on all HDTVs.","description":"Motion Interpolation was an effect that was created to reduce motion blur on HDTVs but a very unfortunate side effect of using this function is that is takes something shot at 24 fps or shot on film and makes it look like it was shot on video at 60i.  In short, it takes the cinematic look out of any image and makes it look like soap opera shot on a cheap video camera.  It is unbelievable that this is a default setting on all HDTVs because essentially what it is doing, is taking the artistic intention away from filmmakers.  As artists, these new HDTVs are preventing our vision from being seen the way we shot it and it\\\'s also affecting the viewer\\\'s experience with the story because they are often put off by the odd "home video" look.  It\\\'s actually very distracting watching a classic like "Five Easy Pieces" and having it look like a sitcom shot on video.nAny filmmaker or film buff should be aware of this and help stop it from being a default setting.  At this stage, the majority of the world are not seeing the films and tv shows as they were intended by the creators.nIt\\\'s fair to have smooth motion as one of the options in the picture settings on HDTVs,  because it actually is a great way to watch sports.  But for literally everything else on tv, it cheapens the look and makes it look as if it\\\'s a soap opera.  If you care about the artistic integrity of the visuals that you watch and appreciate cinematography and a cinematic experience, then you should sign this petition. And if you don\\\'t care about visuals and you only care about story, you should still sign this petition because the visuals are there to set the mood for you to get into the story.nAs a consumer, you should know that this function is ruining the theatrical experience that you are supposedly paying for when you purchase these expensive HDTVs.  Don\\\'t you want to see the films and tv shows as the filmmakers intended you to see them- how beautiful and rich they look in the movie theater?  If you are going to spend most of your time at home watching movies on your television, don\\\'t you want it to be as much of a theatrical experience as possible?nA further irony is also that some of the manufacturers of these HDTVs (Sony and Panasonic) also manufacture the high end digital cameras that shoot in 24fps to give a more cinematic "film" look and they are the very same people negating that artistic choice.  For a more in depth explanation on motion interpolation, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motion_interpolation.nFor all the technological advances we have made in our industry, it\\\'s as if we\\\'re taking a million huge steps backwards in terms of the look of the image by allowing motion interpolation to be a default setting. nThe Ideal:nManufacturers working together with broadcasters to create a way for the signal to automatically switch on "smooth motion" when sports are on tv.  And the signal would switch OFF smooth motion for everything else, allowing everything to look it\\\'s best on tv.  nSmooth motion is also known as auto motion, motion boost, HD natural motion, digital clearmotion, TruMotion, smooth 120 Hz, Intelligent frame creation, etc.n nHERE IS A LINK TO ASSIST IN TURNING OFF THE MOTION INTERPOLATION ON YOUR TV:nhttp://lifehacker.com/disable-motion-smoothing-to-get-rid-of-soap-opera-effe-1526424116n n ","targeting_description":"HDTV Manufacturers/ Broadcasters","letter_body":"Please STOP making Smooth Motion the DEFAULT setting on all HDTVs.","end_date":"2016-11-17","goal":null,"relevant_location":{"city":null,"country_code":"US","lat":null,"lng":null,"state_code":null,"google_places_id":null,"photo_id":null},"restricted_location":null,"slug":"hdtv-manufacturers-please-stop-making-smooth-motion-the-default-setting-on-all-hdtvs","status":"published","victory_date":null,"victory_description":"","is_verified_victory":false,"is_victory":false,"video":null,"is_pledge":false,"topic":null,"tags":[{"id":44549,"locale":"en-US","name":"business and brands","slug":"business-and-brands-en-us","total_count":null,"photo_id":null,"discoverable":null,"created_by_staff_member":true},{"id":51821,"locale":"en-US","name":"modify product","slug":"modify-product-en-us","total_count":null,"photo_id":null,"discoverable":null,"created_by_staff_member":true},{"id":7482,"locale":"en-US","name":"entertainment","slug":"entertainment-11","total_count":null,"photo_id":139992269,"discoverable":null,"created_by_staff_member":true}],"discoverable":true,"total_signature_count":11486,