at shoot in 24fps to give a more cinematic "film" look and they are the very same people negating that artistic choice.  For a more in depth explanation on motion interpolation, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motion_interpolation.nFor all the technological advances we have made in our industry, it\\\'s as if we\\\'re taking a million huge steps backwards in terms of the look of the image by allowing motion interpolation to be a default setting. nThe Ideal:nManufacturers working together with broadcasters to create a way for the signal to automatically switch on "smooth motion" when sports are on tv.  And the signal would switch OFF smooth motion for everything else, allowing everything to look it\\\'s best on tv.  nSmooth motion is also known as auto motion, motion boost, HD natural motion, digital clearmotion, TruMotion, smooth 120 Hz, Intelligent frame creation, etc.n nHERE IS A LINK TO ASSIST IN TURNING OFF THE MOTION INTERPOLATION ON YOUR TV:nhttp://lifehacker.com/disable-motion-smoothing-to-get-rid-of-soap-opera-effe-1526424116n n ","targeting_description":"HDTV Manufacturers/ Broadcasters","letter_body":"Please STOP making Smooth Motion the DEFAULT setting on all HDTVs.","end_date":"2016-11-17","goal":null,"relevant_location":{"city":null,"country_code":"US","lat":null,"lng":null,"state_code":null,"google_places_id":null,"photo_id":null},"restricted_location":null,"slug":"hdtv-manufacturers-please-stop-making-smooth-motion-the-default-setting-on-all-hdtvs","status":"published","victory_date":null,"victory_description":"","is_verified_victory":false,"is_victory":false,"video":null,"is_pledge":false,"topic":null,"tags":[{"id":44549,"locale":"en-US","name":"business and brands","slug":"business-and-brands-en-us","total_count":null,"photo_id":null,"discoverable":null,"created_by_staff_member":true},{"id":51821,"locale":"en-US","name":"modify product","slug":"modify-product-en-us","total_count":null,"photo_id":null,"discoverable":null,"created_by_staff_member":tr